Defendant Mitchell T Picord in court with attorney Eric R. Hart.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Defendant has successfully completed drug treatment court.  The State moves to amend count 1 to a misdemeanor of possession of an amphetamine 961.41(3g)(d).  The Court amends the charge accordingly. 

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

5 MONTHS JAIL (CREDIT - 38 days if revoked), consecutive to present sentence;


TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Perform 40 Hours Community Service. 
*Participate in alumni group.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00(to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
